OL,6,FThe judge, Recorder Peter Makepeace
OL,7,FKC, paid tribute to the bravery of the
OL,8,Fstaff member, telling Lewis: "He is in
OL,9,Fstark contrast to you... he should be
OL,10,Fcommended by the court for his
OL,11,Fbravery."
OL,13,FLewis was jailed for 18 months and
OL,14,Fbanned from driving for two years and
OL,15,Fseven months.
OL,17,FThe shop confirmed the employee was
OL,18,F"shaken up" but not injured.
